ðŸš€ 1. Setup & Import
code
Python
import numpy as np  # The standard industry convention
ðŸ—ï¸ 2. Array Creation
Command	Description
np.array([1, 2, 3])	Create a 1D array
np.array([(1,2,3),(4,5,6)])	Create a 2D array (Matrix)
np.zeros((3, 4))	Create an array of zeros (3 rows, 4 cols)
np.ones((2, 3))	Create an array of ones
np.eye(4)	Create a 4x4 Identity Matrix
np.arange(0, 10, 2)	Array from 0 to 10 with step 2
np.linspace(0, 1, 5)	5 evenly spaced values between 0 and 1
np.random.rand(3,3)	3x3 array of random floats (0-1)
ðŸ” 3. Inspecting Your Data
code
Python
arr.shape    # Dimensions (rows, columns)
arr.len()    # Length of first dimension
arr.ndim     # Number of dimensions
arr.size     # Number of elements
arr.dtype    # Data type (int64, float64, etc.)
arr.astype(float) # Convert array to a different type
[1][2][3]
âœ‚ï¸ 4. Indexing & Slicing
arr[0]: Get element at index 0.
arr[1, 2]: Get element at row 1, column 2.[2][4]
arr[0:3]: Get elements from index 0 to 2.
arr[: , 1]: Get all rows from column 1.
arr[arr > 5]: Boolean Indexing (returns values greater than 5).
ðŸ”„ 5. Array Manipulation
Function	What it does
arr.reshape(3, -1)	Reshape data (let NumPy calculate columns)
arr.flatten()	Collapse a multi-dimensional array into 1D
arr.T or arr.transpose()	Transpose the matrix (swap rows/cols)
np.concatenate((a, b))	Join two arrays
np.vstack((a, b))	Stack arrays vertically
np.hstack((a, b))	Stack arrays horizontally
ðŸ”¢ 6. Mathematical Operations (Vectorization)
code
Python
# Element-wise operations
np.add(a, b)      # a + b
np.subtract(a, b) # a - b
np.multiply(a, b) # a * b
np.divide(a, b)   # a / b
np.exp(a)         # Exponential
np.sqrt(a)        # Square root
ðŸ“Š 7. Basic Statistics
Method	Description
arr.sum()	Sum of all elements
arr.mean()	Average value
arr.std()	Standard Deviation
arr.min() / arr.max()	Find range boundaries
arr.argmin()	Index of the minimum value
np.median(arr)	Find the middle value
ðŸ’¾ 8. Saving & Loading
code
Python
np.save('my_array.npy', arr)    # Save to binary file
arr = np.load('my_array.npy')   # Load from binary file
np.savetxt('data.csv', arr, delimiter=',') # Save as CSV

